Simplified the optimization class, added intensity distributions

Merged the multiobjective function and single objective to run_optimization:

* All optimizers use combined objective as their main objective function
* Combined objective keeps track of individual function evaluations now
* All functions take intensity instead of parameters now
* Optimizer basically generates intensity and uses it for any downstream objective function, previously it generated intensity for each function: Now they use the same 1 intensity vec  per iteration instead of 1 intensity vec per objective function per iteration.

Added capability to change the location of the epitope

The code only considered the first index of the epitope tag for the location, added the option to now use the middle of the epitope for the intensity vector, or the back of the epitope.

for example:

with tag DDYDDK:

NNNN DDYDDK NNNN

front: tag_epitopes = [4]

back: tag_epitopes = [10]

middle: tag_epitopes = [7]

This effects the intensity vector by changing the probe vector by an offset.

Changed the setup / module files to ignore cpp if not compiled

* setup.py now trys two methods to compile
